<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-06-1066 </DOCNO><TEXT>The local cogeneration plant supplying a local community sized down to1000 dwellings with heat and feeding electricity into the public gridis a new element in the Danish energy policy. In June 1986 an agreementbetween the Danish government (conservative - liberal coalition) andthe labour party was concluded about the future extension of the electricitygenerating system and an intensified action in the field of energy savings.The extension of the electricity generating system should include thebuilding of local cogeneration plants as far as possible. (EG).</TEXT></DOC>